text.tspan: In peer-to-peer (P2P) systems, all participating network nodes contribute to the total functions and
services offered by the system. To achieve this, the nodes are interconnected by an application specific
overlay network. All nodes can thus be said to operate as both clients and servers. This result in
decentralisation and loss dependence on the reachability of individual nodes.
